 TOUGH2 IS A PROGRAM FOR NON-ISOTHERMAL MULTIPHASE MULTICOMPONENT FLOW IN PERMEABLE MEDIA. IT IS A MEMBER OF THE MULKOM FAMILY OF CODES DEVELOPED AT LBNL.

 PROGRAM TOUGHREACT 2.0, 2009.3.30
 Special version for conjugate gradient package T2CG2, includes definition of coordinate arrays and radiative heat transfer capability.

 PARAMETERS FOR FLEXIBLE DIMENSIONING OF MAJOR ARRAYS (MAIN PROGRAM): MNEQ =  4   MNK =  3   MNPH =  2   MNB = 12

 MAXIMUM NUMBER OF VOLUME ELEMENTS (GRID BLOCKS) AND CONNECTIONS (INTERFACES):   50000   180000
 MAXIMUM LENGTH OF PRIMARY VARIABLE ARRAYS (MPRIM):  200000
 MAXIMUM NUMBER OF GENERATION (SINKS/SOURCES) ITEMS (MNOGN):     200
 MAXIMUM NUMBER OF TABULAR (TIME-DEPENDENT) GENERATION DATA   10000
 LENGTH OF SECONDARY PARAMETER ARRAY (MSEC): 8000000
 MAXIMUM NUMBER OF JACOBIAN MATRIX ELEMENTS (MNZ): 6560000

 LARGE LINEAR EQUATION ARRAYS: LENGTH OF IRN = 6560000 LENGTH OF ICN AND CO =  6560000

 array dimensioning is made according to the needs of the conjugate gradient solvers when using LUBAND, only a smaller-size problem can be accommodated
 restriction with MA28 is: NEL+2*NCON<{MNEL+2*MNCON}/4

 ************************************************************call subroutine IO in t2cg22_v2.f************************************************************
 IO 1.0, 1991.4.15: READ DISK FILES:

 FILE *MESH* EXISTS --- OPEN AS AN OLD FILE
 FILE *INCON* EXISTS --- OPEN AS AN OLD FILE
 FILE *GENER* EXISTS --- OPEN AS AN OLD FILE
 FILE *SAVE* EXISTS --- OPEN AS AN OLD FILE
 FILE *LINEQ* EXISTS --- OPEN AS AN OLD FILE
 TITLE:# A EOS1 tracer test problem                                                    

 ************************************************************call subroutine INPUT in t2f_v2.f************************************************************
 INPUT 1.50, 2000.5.25: READ DATA PROVIDED THROUGH flow.inp

 DOMAIN NO.  1: ROCK1
 DOMAIN NO.  2: ROCK2
     
 WRITE FILE *GENER* FROM INPUT DATA

 ************************************************************call subroutine flop in t2cg22_v2.f************************************************************
 FLOP 1.0, 1991.4.11: CALCULATE NUMBER OF SIGNIFICANT DIGITS FOR FLOATING POINT ARITHMETIC
 FLOATING POINT PROCESSOR HAS APPROXIMATELY 15 SIGNIFICANT DIGITS
 USE DEFAULT DFAC=0.1051E-07

 ************************************************************call subroutine rfile in t2f_v2.f************************************************************
 RFILE 1.5, 1999.6.18: initializes permeability modifiers and coordinate arrays, and optionally reads tables with flowing wellbore pressures from disk files
 
 all NCON =   1044 connections read from file *MESH* reference known elements, and have been initialized to the data arrays

 +++subroutine pmin in t2f_v2.f is called+++
 PMIN 1.0, 1997.9.26: initialize block-by-block permeability modifiers
 domain = "SEED " is not present, no permeability modification will be made
 +++end of call subroutine pmin+++

 MESH HAS    362 ELEMENTS (    362 ACTIVE) AND   1044 CONNECTIONS (INTERFACES) BETWEEN THEM, GENER HAS     2 SINKS/SOURCES
  ****call subroutine sinsub in t2cg22_v2.f****
 SIN 1.00, 1999.10.1: initialize parameters for the solver package, and generate informative printout
  ****end of call subroutine sinsub****

 ------------------------------------------------------------call CYCIT for simulation------------------------------------------------------------
 CYCIT 1.01, 1998.5.28: EXECUTIVE ROUTINE OF TOUGH2

 EOS 1.1, 2009.3.20: *EOS1* ... THERMOPHYSICAL PROPERTIES MODULE FOR WATER
 EOS1: EQUATION OF STATE FOR WATER (OPTIONAL: TWO-WATER MIXTURES)

 OPTIONS SELECTED ARE: (NK,NEQ,NPH,NB) = (1,2,2,8)
 WHERE NK - NUMBER OF FLUID COMPONENTS, NEQ - NUMBER OF EQUATIONS PER GRID BLOCK, NPH - NUMBER OF PHASES THAT CAN BE PRESENT, NB - NUMBER OF SECONDARY PARAMETERS (OTHER THAN COMPONENT MASS FRACTIONS)

 disable diffusion when NK = 1 or NB = 6; enable when NK = 2 and NB = 8

 AVAILABLE OPTIONS ARE (NK,NEQ,NPH,NB) = 
 (1,2,2,6 or 8) - ONE WATER COMPONENT, NON-ISOTHERMAL (DEFAULT:1,2,2,6)
 (1,1,2,6 or 8) - SINGLE PHASE(LIQUID OR VAPOR), ISOTHERMAL
 (2,3,2,6 or 8) - TWO WATERS (NON-ISOTHERMAL ONLY)

 POSSIBLE PRIMARY VARIABLES ARE:
 P - PRESSURE, T - TEMPERATURE, S - GAS PHASE SATURATION
 PRIMARY VARIABLES COMBINITIONS IN DIFFERENT PHASE CONDITIONS: SINGLE-PHASE: P,T; TWO-PHASE: P,S

 +++++acquire Psat with given TX in t2f_v2.f+++++
 SAT 1.0S, 1990.9.17: STEAM TABLE EQUATION: SATURATION PRESSURE AS FUNCTION OF TEMPERATURE (M. OS.)
 VISW 1.0, 1990.1.22: VISCOSITY OF LIQUID WATER AS FUNCTION OF TEMPERATURE AND PRESSURE
      COWAT 1.0S, 1990.9.17: LIQUID WATER DENSITY AND INT. ENERGY VERSUS TEMPERATURE AND PRESSURE (M. OS.)
 SUPST 1.0S, 1991.2.1: VAPOR DENSITY AND INT. ENERGY AS FUNCTION OF TEMPERATURE AND PRESSURE (M. OS.)
 PCAP 1.1, 2009.4.14: CAPILLARY PRESSURE AS FUNCTION OF SATURATION
 ******BALLA 1.0, 1990.1.22: PERFORM SUMMARY BALANCES FOR' VOLUME, MASS AND ENERGY**********

 VOLUME- AND MASS-BALANCES: IN [KCYC,ITER,TIME(SECONDS)] = [  96,  0, 0.43200E+04]

 PHASE VOLUMES (M^3): GAS 0.00000E+00; AQUEOUS 0.32000E+03

 MASS (KG): GAS 0.00000E+00; AQUEOUS 0.28543E+06 TOTAL H2O 0.28543E+06 KG;  H2O(2) 0.00000E+00 KG; INT. ENERGY 0.22896E+12 J
 *******READ TRANSPORT AND CHEMISTRY*******
 *****read solute.inp in readsolu_v2.f*****
 READSOLU 1.0, 2008.2.6: Read input data for solute transport
 ****read chemistry input data in inichm_v2.f****
 init 1.0, 2008.2.6: Read and initialize chemical input data
 ****readtherm_hkf, 2008.2.2: Read chemical thermodynamic' database*************
 ********echotherm 1.0, 2003.7.30: Echo all data read in chemical thermodynamic database********
 **********assign 1.0, 2003.7.30: Assigns logK values to each reaction**********
 ***** nrinit 1.0, 2003.7.30: Solve initial chemical system by Newton-Raphson iteration
 dh_hkf81 1.0, 2003.7.30: Calculate activity coefficient of aqueous species in geochem_v2.f
 cs_cp 1.0: 2003.7.30: Calculate total concentrations and partial derivatives in geochem_v2.f
 cmq_cp 1.0, 2003.7.30: Calculate saturation indexes of minerals in geochem_v2.f
 cr_cp 1.0: 2003.7.30: Calculate mineral reaction rates and their derivative in geochem_v2.f
 ***** jacobinit 1.0, 2003.7.30: Construct Jacobian matrix for initial chemical system
 *************** CHDUMP 1.01: 2006.3.23: Write chemical speciation data in geochem_v2.f***************
 ***convert indices to names in readsolu_v2.f***
 READ_RESTART 1.0, 2003.7.30: Read restart data for reactive chemical transport
 ***********MAIN ITERATIVE SIMULATION***************
 TSTEP 1.0, 1991.3.4: ADJUST TIME STEPS TO COINCIDE WITH USER-DEFINED TARGET TIMES
 **MULTI 1.2, 2009.3.20: ASSEMBLE ALL ACCUMULATION AND FLOW TERMS, includes capabilities for radiative heat transfer and diffusion in all phases with local equilibrium phase partitioning between gas and liquid, allows block-by-block permeability modification***************
 **QU 1.1, 1998.1.23: ASSEMBLE SOURCE AND SINK TERMS,"rigorous" step rate capability for MOP(12) = 2, and capability for flowing wellbore pressure corrections******
 ***PHASD 1.0, 2001.4.23: calculate composition, rate and' enthalpy for wells on deliverability*********
 ********QLOSS 1.01, 1995.1.10: PERFORM SEMI-ANALYTICAL CALCULATION FOR HEAT EXCHANGE WITH CONFINING BEDS**********

 PERFORM SEMI-ANALYTICAL HEAT EXCHANGE CALCULATION
 THERMAL PARAMETERS ARE:
 TEMPERATURE =  0.19350E+03 HEAT CONDUCTIVITY =  0.30000E+01 DENSITY =  0.26000E+04 SPECIFIC HEAT =  0.92000E+03 DIFFUSIVITY =  0.12542E-05


 LINEQ 2.00, 1999.10.4: Interface for linear equation solvers T2CG2, Can call a direct solver or a package of conjugate gradient solvers
 ***CONVER2 1.0, 2003.7.4: UPDATE PRIMARY VARIABLES AFTER' CONVERGENCE IS ACHIEVED (Used when coupled with reactive geochemistry)************
